The paper deals with information theory and signal processing, specifically the capacity loss in analog channels under sub-Nyquist sampling. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves optimization and minimax theory, which could fall under cs.MM (Mathematical Optimization) and cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with sub-Nyquist sampling, which could also fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
